The paper presents a framework for incorporating domain knowledge into topic modeling through an interactive visual analytics workspace. This involves identifying and refining semantic concept spaces using word-embedding projections. The paper is focused on the intersection of human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL), with applications in information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
